&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bank Emergency Nurse Practitioner Band: 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced Emergency Nurse Practitioner looking for some flexible working hours?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are, we’d love to hear from you. We need highly motivated professional individuals with a passion for improving both our patients care and experience, to join our team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As an Emergency Nurse Practitioner, you will be a &lt;/span&gt;clinical expert who can &lt;strong&gt;work autonomously&lt;/strong&gt; providing patient-centred clinical care, encompassing the skills of assessment, examination, diagnosis, treatment and/or referral and discharge to patients with minor injuries and illnesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Surrey NHS Foundation Trust Emergency Department sees approximately 75000 patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that you will need to attend the next available Assessment Centre. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact k.araya@nhs.net or contact the Temporary Staffing Recruitment team rsch.jointhebank@nhs.net.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
